!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

tendency /ˈtɛndənsɪ/

(tendencies) 

1. N-COUNT A tendency is a worrying or unpleasant habit or action that keeps occurring. 倾向 

例： ...the government's tendency to secrecy in recent years. …近年来政府的保密倾向。 

2. N-COUNT A tendency is a part of your character that makes you often behave in an unpleasant or worrying way. (性格方面不好的) 倾向 

例： He is spoiled, arrogant and has a tendency toward snobbery. 他被宠坏了，很傲慢，而且有势利倾向。

</div>

